data.chText: 斯诺克（供两人打的落袋台球，打球人用球杆打白色母球，按一定顺序撞15个红球和6个其他颜色的球入袋）
data.enText: a game for two people played on a long table covered with green cloth. Players use cues (= long sticks) to hit a white ball against other balls (15 red and 6 of other colours) in order to get the coloured balls into pockets at the edge of the table, in a particular set order.

data.chText: 斯诺克厅、斯诺克运动员、斯诺克球桌等

data.enText: a position in snooker in which one player has made it very difficult for the opponent to play a shot within the rules
to have your opponent in a snooker(2)
to make it impossible for sb to do sth, especially sth they want to do

data.chText: 我原先设想的各项周末计划，这时候就彻底落空了。
data.enText: Any plans I'd had for the weekend were by now well and truly snookered.

word_means: 斯诺克(供两人打的落袋台球，打球人用球杆打白色母球，按一定顺序撞15个红球和6个其他颜色的球入袋)

means: 斯诺克(供两人打的落袋台球，打球人用球杆打白色母球，按一定顺序撞15个红球和6个其他颜色的球入袋)

tr: a form of pool played with 15 red balls and six balls of other colors and a cue ball
leave one's opponent unable to take a direct shot

example: He was snookered by the con-man's smooth talk

value.def: Snooker is a game involving balls on a large table. The players use a long stick to hit a white ball, and score points by knocking coloured balls into the pockets at the sides of the table.
If you are snookered by something, it is difficult or impossible for you to take action or do what you want to do.

example.ex: The President has been snookered on this issue.
example.tran: 在这个问题上，总统未能如愿。

value.tran: 阻止…采取行动;使…不如愿
